<item>
            <title>[LU-5272] Test failure on test suite sanity-scrub, subtest test_10a</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5272</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/b39559ca-fe8b-11e3-a668-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/b39559ca-fe8b-11e3-a668-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;maloo search shows only a couple of recent instances of this failure.  The other is &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/38525c26-fe87-11e3-a668-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/38525c26-fe87-11e3-a668-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.  Very different mods being tested which makes me guess the failure isn&apos;t related to the patch under test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both instances happened on the same day, 6/28.  Makes me suspicious that a recent master landing may be causing this to start happening suddenly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_10a failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;test failed to respond and timed out&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity-scrub 10a&lt;/p&gt;</description>
